Class PIParserBase

      • getAttribute

        protected String getAttribute(ProcessingInstruction pi,
                              String name,
                              boolean required)
        Extracts an attribute from a processing instruction's data where the data is formatted as a space-delimited list of key-value pairs.
        Parameters:
        pi - The processing instruction.
        name - The attribute's key.
        required - If true and the attributes is not found, an exception is throw.
        Returns:
        The attribute's value. If the attribute is not found, null will be returned unless the required parameter is true, in which case an exception is thrown.
